The '''1950 Kentucky Wildcats football team''' represented the [[University of Kentucky]] in the [[1950 college football season]]. The offense scored 393 points while the defense allowed 69 points. Led by head coach [[Bear Bryant]], the Wildcats were the [[Southeastern Conference|SEC]] champions and by winning the [[1951 Sugar Bowl|Sugar Bowl]] were listed as the #1 ranked team 40 years later in a computer ranking produced by Jeff Sagarin.
==Season== The 1950 Kentucky team concluded its season with a victory over [[Bud Wilkinson]]'s #1 ranked and NCAA champion [[1950 Oklahoma Sooners football team|Oklahoma Sooners]] in the Sugar Bowl. The living players from the 1950 Wildcats team were honored during halftime of a game during the 2005 season as the #1 ranked team for the 1950 season, even though they finished the season ranked #7 by the AP. In 1990, Jeff Sagarin released a retroactive ranking of teams for the 1950 season and Kentucky was listed #1. ===Schedule=== {|class="wikitable" width="80%" |- align="center" style="background: blue;color:#FFFFFF;" | '''Game''' || '''Date''' || '''Opponent''' || '''Result''' || '''Wildcats points''' || '''Opponents''' || '''Record''' |- align="center" bgcolor="" | 1 ||Sept. 16 ||North Texas ||Win || 25 || 0|| 1-0, #6 |- align="center" bgcolor="" | 2 ||Sept. 23 || Louisiana State ||Win || 14 || 0 || 2-0, #5 |- align="center" bgcolor="" | 3 ||Sept. 30|| [[Ole Miss Rebels football|Mississippi]] ||Win || 27 || 0 ||3-0, #6 |- align="center" bgcolor="" | 4 ||Oct 7 || Dayton ||Win || 40 || 0 ||4-0, #5 |- align="center" bgcolor="" | 5 ||Oct. 14 || [[Cincinnati Bearcats football|Cincinnati]] || Win|| 41 || 7 ||5-0, #4 |- align="center" bgcolor="" | 6 ||Oct. 21 || at Villanova || Win|| 34 || 7 ||6-0, #4 |- align="center" bgcolor="" | 7 || Oct. 28 || at Georgia Tech ||Win || 28 || 14 ||7-0, #5 |- align="center" bgcolor="" | 8 ||Nov. 4|| #17 [[1950 Florida Gators football team|Florida]] ||Win || 40 || 6 ||8-0, #4 |- align="center" bgcolor="" | 9 ||Nov. 11|| at Mississippi State ||Win|| 48 || 21 ||9-0, #5 |- align="center" bgcolor="" | 10 ||Nov. 18 || North Dakota ||Win || 83 || 0 ||10-0, #3 |- align="center" bgcolor="" | 11 ||Nov. 25 || at #9 Tennessee ||Loss || 0 || 7 ||10-1, #7 |- align="center" bgcolor="" | 12 ||Jan. 1 || #1 Oklahoma ||Win || 13 || 7 ||11-1 |- align="center" bgcolor="" |} <ref>http://cfreference.net/cfr/school.s?id=184&season=1950</ref><ref>1997 Kentucky Wi